  <title>ZIMBABWE: Admin Lines</title>
  <abstract>The dataset was created by converting the Zimbabwe Admin3 polygon layer to lines

Administrative boundary lines for Zimbabwe admin level 0-3. Each line is attributed with the highest Admin level that it can represent. These lines can be helpful for cartographic purposes.</abstract>

  <history>Layer was created by ITOS by converting the Zimbabwe Admin2 polygon layer to lines. The lines were created after all processing on the admin layer had been completed by ITOS. An 'AdminLevel' field is used to attribute the lines. The values used for this field are: (0,1,2,3,4,5,99). 99 represents coastline. 0 is international border, 1 is Admin1 border, 2 is Admin2 border, etc. Each line is attributed with the highest admin level that it can participate in.</history>
